:"Remove pancake batter from refrigerator and mix with spatula. Place a medium-sized non-stick frying pan over medium-high heat. Place a little butter or oil into hot pan and pour in a small ladle of pancake mixture. Cook for 3 minutes, or until bubbles form on top of pancake then flip and cook for a further 3 minutes, or until browned. Set pancake aside and cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Repeat with remaining batter to make approx. 16 pancakes, mixing the batter occasionally with spatula between batches to keep batter smooth."},{"content":"Remove vanilla bean pods and cinnamon sticks from reserved poached apples. Serve pancakes hot topped with poached apples and syrup."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a decadent dessert, serve pancakes with blueberries and fresh cream or raspberries and vanilla bean ice cream.","For a lactose-free version, ensure you use grapeseed oil rather than butter for frying, and a dairy-free milk, such as nut or coconut milk."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 25m","16 pieces"]}